en_969786_0	Minister Sajith Premadasa says that he will not use public funds for his maintenance if he becomes the President.
en_969786_1	He was speaking at a public meeting in Mortuwella area.
en_969786_2	A public rally to ensure the victory of the Democratic Front presidential candidate at the presidential election took place at Moratuwa, Moratuwella area under the patronage of Minister Sajith Premadasa.
en_969786_3	A large group of people including State Minister Eran Wickremarathne were present at the meeting.
en_969786_4	Minister Sajith Premadasa said that he will take measures to become the President who used the least amount of public money for his maintenance.
en_969786_5	He said that he will not become a President who will draw a salary from the tax money paid by the people.
en_969786_6	He said he will also not get other perks and privileges.
en_969786_7	He further said that he will send back all those payments back to the Treasury and even use his salary to work for the people.
en_969786_8	He added that he expect to sign a social agreement with the people.
en_969786_9	The Minister said that he will make available the benefits of the development to the people.
